{"id": 6650, "title": "Ticket #6650: Update boost external", "description": "<blockquote>\nLet's get the externals up to date. Only address boost with this release.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2018-Apr-13 14:16:07 by gthain:</em> <br/>\n\nNote that the boost 1.66 external doesn't build on csl supported machine, as they have an old numpy installed.  Reverting this for now, so I can continue to build and push.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Apr-13 16:42</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/87fb839f45b1ad017b098afedc39cc1eec547cdd\">[54718]</a></span>: Disable numpy support in the boost python module. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6650\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6650'); return false;\" title=\"Update boost external\">#6650</a></span> The version of numpy on some of our older platforms (rhel6) is too old for boost 1.66. I couldn't find a flag to disable just the numpy support in boost, so I resorted to hacking the boost build tools to think numpy isn't installed.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Apr-13 16:41</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/e915da2be0934b19bbaf9f6ea587a225f09dccd9\">[54717]</a></span>: Revert \"Revert \"(<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6650\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6650'); return